{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5f93030c-435b-41f0-a01a-95c6ff7ed339","content":"There's no pipeline file in the workspace, so here's a general migration guide:\n\n## Key changes\n\n**1. Replace `VSTest@3` with `DotNetCoreCLI@2` (or a plain `dotnet test` script)**\n\nMicrosoft.Testing.Platform runs via `dotnet test` — there's no separate test adapter step.\n\n**2. Enable TRX reports**\n\nPass `--logger trx` so `.trx` files are still produced:\n\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --logger trx\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n```\n\n**3. Publish test results**\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish test results'\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest   # TRX is the \"VSTest\" format\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n  condition: succeededOrFailed()\n```\n\n**4. Collect code coverage**\n\nAdd `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` (or use Coverlet):\n\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests with coverage'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --logger trx\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n## Summary of what to remove / add\n\n| Before (VSTest@3) | After |\n|---|---|\n| `VSTest@3` task | `DotNetCoreCLI@2` with `command: test` |\n| Built-in result publishing | Explicit `PublishTestResults@2` |\n| `codeCoverageEnabled: true` | `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` + `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2` |\n\n> **Tip:** Ensure your test projects reference `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` if using Microsoft.Testing.Platform directly (not the VSTest bridge). For the VSTest compatibility bridge, `--logger trx` works out of the box.\n\nWould you like me to create a sample pipeline YAML file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2e76c75d-c944-48f0-a624-f0fbcf3ba7bb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty - no existing repository or pipeline files to inspect. The user is asking a general question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in an Azure DevOps CI pipeline while keeping TRX reports and code coverage. I'll provide a concise but complete answer.","outputTokens":701,"requestId":"702D:9F427:DB37D4B:F17DFED:69F2A85F"},"id":"d6c643f2-a681-46c9-b878-ec4fbdd64e41","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:55:09.872Z","parentId":"abe98159-bb30-4781-9ffc-866b7a20a862"}
